<br>
Now I wondered how would the best tactic be to use this? I imagine that basically you wait until your (earth) pet is a bit over your safety margin, then let it root your opponent once more, and reclaim it. Immeditaly followed by summoning a new pet.<br>
<br>
Is the key of this tactic to give up the safety of having a pet up at all times (normal chaining) for the improved mana? Or can you change this tactic in a way to avoid being petless?<br>
<br>
How would Suspend Minion play into this, can you use the skill as a safety net while being beat on (speak can you be interrupted while unsuspending your pet)?<br>
<br>
