<br>
Pull mob with Burst of Flame or Shock of Blades, Malosini the mob after sending in the pet.  If you have Spec Conj 200, SCM 3, and a Summoning Efficiency 3 (or 4) item, you will have enough mana to buff the pet with either Burnout or a Cadeau.  You can stand the whole time if you choose.<br>
<br>
Usually once the pet is below half hps, I wait for the pet to root one more time (ideally I am close enough to the mob to see whether or not root has taken hold), then click on my Torch of Alna.  I immediately resummon (I wear a Kobold Jester's Crown and have recently gotten Quick Summoning 2, for 5 second pets).  While summoning, I type out /pet kill  (then the first letter or two of the mob's name) then hit Enter when pet is finished being resummoned.  While the pet is attacking, I rebuff the pet.<br>
<br>
Advantage #1:  virtually mana free resummoning of pets (add Elemental Pact and it also becomes reagant free as well)<br>
<br>
Advantage #2:  you can throw a single buff on the pet without being concerned about your mana pool<br>
<br>
Advantage #3:  scales with more magicians, adding even one more IR magician will obviate Disadvantage #1 and 3, and minimize Disadvantage #2<br>
<br>
Disadvantage #1:  Pet root breaks, and you will be forced to Channel a resummon.  You will also take damage.<br>
<br>
Disadvantage #2:  Nuking is not recommended for the same reason as regular chaining:  pet will have to overcome your aggro<br>
<br>
Disadvantage #3:  Good luck trying not to get summoned (by mobs that summon) between pets.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Here are things you can do or use to increase the safety of the tactic:<br>
<br>
1.  Get a rt click &quot;Blind&quot; type spell item.  Shaderock Robe or Bioluminescent Orb are good examples of this.<br>
<br>
2.  Add a second magician (of course).  Even if all the second magician can do is send a pet in while you are resummoning, then you have significantly increased the safety of the tactic.<br>
<br>
3.  Train in Quick Summoning, Channeling Focus, Combat Agility, and/or Combat Stability to better deal with root breaks.<br>
<br>
The key to the tactic solo is the potency of the pet's root spell.  If the pet can't root it, you probably can't solo it using this method. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A> at: 12/12/02 6:17:36 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=466.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=466.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=466.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.threadControl?topicID=466.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=466.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=466.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm